## Conclusion\
\
DiaFoot.AI v2 is a feasible and well-scoped computer vision system design for this course project. The selected cascaded architecture is justified by both practical workflow needs and ablation evidence. The project\'92s strongest methodological contribution is not only model performance but also its data governance and robustness-oriented evaluation structure. Current results indicate strong segmentation capability on DFU-focused tasks, alongside a clear and important challenge in cross-domain triage generalization. The final project will therefore prioritize robust classifier improvement, transparent reporting, reproducibility, and responsible claim boundaries. This approach aligns with professional AI engineering standards and with the rubric dimensions of purpose, scope, research depth, design quality, implementation strategy, and writing quality.\
